<HEADLINE> Third-Seeded Gambill Out for Injury in Shanghai Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Third seed Michael Tebbutt of
the United States failed to make the last eight as he walked out
for a back injury on Thursday in the Shanghai Open ATP Tour.
</P>
<P>
Gambill stopped at 5-0 in the first set of the match against M
ichael Tebbutt of Australia when the back injury, which he
suffered during the Davis Cup competition, betrayed him.
</P>
<P>
Tebbutt now faces his quarter-final rival Ramon Delgado of
Paraguay, who stormed back from one set down to dispose off
Indian Leander Paes, 2-6, 6-3, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Australian Mark Woodforde is now one step away from a matchup
with his world No.1 doulbes partner, Todd Woodbridge, after he
beat Sargis Sargsian of Armenia 6-2, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde will meet fifth-seeded Paul Haarhuis of the
Netherlands, who defeated German Karsten Braasch 6-0, 6-3
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The victory for Woodforde sets up a semi-final vie against the
winner of a tie between Woodbridge and American second-seeded
Michael Chang, 
</P>
</TEXT>
