<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Owners, Union Meet Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The NBA and its player union
resume collective bargaining negotiations Thursday in New York in
a last-ditch effort to keep intact the league's record of not
ever having lost a regular-season game to a work stoppage.
</P>
<P>
The owner-imposed lockout, in effect since midnight June 30,
already has led to the pre-season schedule being canceled and the
open of training camps being postponed.
</P>
<P>
The lack of progress in negotiations - the sides have had one
bargaining session since the lockout started - makes it
increasingly doubtful if the season will start on November 3.
</P>
<P>
"I was more optimistic than pessimistic over the summer, but
lately that has turned around," said Seattle center Jim
McIlvaine, union secretary-treasurer.
</P>
<P>
"This meeting will be big, the only way we're going to get
started on time."
</P>
<P>
Said Indiana Pacers forward Mark Pope, "Opening the season on
time seems like it would take a miracle, and I don't see one
coming."
</P>
<P>
The league will make a decision on canceling regular-season
games next week.
</P>
<P>
Neither side is optimistic much progress will be made during
today's session. Union executive director Billy Hunter has said
he won't present a counterproposal to the league's most recent
offer, made almost two weeks ago, because it was the same as the
previous one.
</P>
<P>
Hunter complained the owners have made "ludicrous" proposals,
and union President Patrick Ewing said the last offer by the
owners was "disrespectful."
</P>
<P>
The key issue blocking an agreement is the salary cap. Owners
say player salaries are increasing faster than revenues and want
a salary cap teams cannot exceed.
</P>
<P>
They proposed eliminating the Larry Bird exception, the clause
in the previous agreement that allowed teams to re-sign their
free agents without regard to salary cap, thus creating a soft
salary cap.
</P>
<P>
The union says the Bird exception is untouchable and will not
negotiate on it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
