<HEADLINE> Olano Wins World Time Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Abraham Olano, a
fresh Tour of Spain winner, won the time trial on Thursday in the
World Cycling Championships in Valkenburg, the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Olano, an Olympic silver medallist, timed 54 minutes 32
seconds on the 43.5 kilometers hilly circuit for a second trophy
in a span of 11 days.
</P>
<P>
Compatriot Melchior Mauri completed the race at second with 37
seconds behind, while Ukrainian Sergei Gontchar was further 10
seconds away in third place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
