<HEADLINE> Egypt's Government Bodies Urged to Buy Local Cars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
on Thursday called on government bodies to buy locally produced
cars in a bid to boost the domestic automobile industry.
</P>
<P>
"The ministries and national agencies should give priority to
the Egyptian car-making industry to cover their needs of passenger
and transportation vehicles instead of having to import them,"
Mubarak said during a visit to the Egypt Achievements Exhibit held
here.
</P>
<P>
He called for more facilities for local automakers to encourage
the domestic car market.
</P>
<P>
"Any top government official who will import a car, provided
that the market is abundant with locally produced vehicles, will
be called into question," he added.
</P>
<P>
Egypt does not manufacture its own cars, leaving the market
crowded with imported cars. The Egyptian National Automotive
Company and private companies have been assembling cars locally in
joint ventures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
