<HEADLINE> Sixteen Policemen Killed in Central India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 16 policemen were
killed and 15 others injured Thursday in a landmine blast
triggered by extremists belonging to the rebel People's War Group
in central India, the Press Trust of India (PTI) said.
</P>
<P>
The policemen were attacked inside a forest in the
newly-created Dantewada district in Madhya Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
The attack is the second major incident since 1994 when
extremists killed seven policemen in a landmine blast. 
</P>
</TEXT>
