<DOCNO> XIE19981009.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece's Inflation Rises to 5.2 Percent in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Greece's inflation increased from
5.0 percent in August to 5.2 percent in September this year,
according to figures released by the Greek National Statistics
Service (NSS) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The NSS attributed the rise in inflation to rising prices in
durable goods, food as well as an increase in education services'
prices.
</P>
<P>
The NSS remained confident that inflation could drop following
the Greek government's measures to contain consumer price
inflation in the last quarter of 1998.
</P>
<P>
To combat inflation, the Greek government has decided to lower
a special fuel and heating oil tax and reduce food price in super
markets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
