<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Accusation of Incursion Baseless: Taliban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban said on
Thursday that Iran's accusation of Taliban incursions was "totally
baseless."
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here from Kabul quoted Taliban spokesman
Maulvi Wakil Ahmad as saying that the Iranian troops had been
shelling near the Afghan border for the last three days with some
missiles landing on Afghan soil.
</P>
<P>
There have been no reports of casualties.
</P>
<P>
Wakil said Iran was doing this to cover up their own violations
of Afghan territory.
</P>
<P>
Gen. Azizollah Jafari, the commander of the Revolutionary
Guards' ground forces, said Taliban militiamen attacked an Iranian
border post in the Saleh-Abad region of Torbat-e-Jam, in the north
of Khorasan province, with machine-guns and artillery on Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
He said his forces inflicted "heavy casualties" on the Taliban
militia during a three-hour clash on the Iran-Afghanistan border.
</P>
<P>
"The Iranian forces responded and the clashes lasted for three
hours," he was quoted by the Iranian News Agency (IRNA) as saying.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
