renewed U.N. efforts to broker peace in the war-ravaged country.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan, Iran, Turkmenistan, Tajikistan, Uzbekistan, China and
Russia and the United States agreed at the U.N. meeting that the
world body should send its representatives to address the
Afghanistan conflict in a peaceful manner.
</P>
<P>
While the Taliban now control over 95 percent of Afghanistan,
the international community has called for a broad-based
government in Kabul. 
