<HEADLINE> Cyprus to Emerge as Regional Services Center, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Cypriot government is
striving to turn Cyprus into a regional services center, President
Glafcos Clerides said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark at the opening ceremony of the
EuroMediterranean Services Exhibition "CyServ '98," which is aimed
at upgrading the island's services industry.
</P>
<P>
Clerides pointed out that the services sector contributes 73
percent to the country's Gross Domestic Product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
Cyprus aims to achieve even better results that will have a
positive effect on all sectors of the country's economic
activity, he added.
</P>
<P>
In his remark, Minister of Commerce, Industry and Tourism
Nicos Rolandis depicted a bright future for further enlargement of
the services sector not only in Cyprus but also in other countries.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the globalization of the economy and the
liberalization of trade have brought about a substantive increase
of productivity of services.
</P>
<P>
Some 30 services companies from Greece, Israel, Egypt, Jordan,
Lebanon and Malta, as well as 50 others from Cyprus are
participating in the four-day exhibition.
</P>
<P>
They include companies and organizations related to the
services sector such as consultancy, accounting, advertizing,
information-technology, market research, banking, tourism and
education. 
</P>
