<HEADLINE> S. Africa Blamed for Repatriating Mozambican </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A Mozambican official Thursday
came out to blast South Africa for repatriating refugees without
notifying the Mozambican side in advance.
</P>
<P>
Noe Mathe, Director of Social Coordination of Maputo Province,
said here that what Pretoria did has brought great pressure on
the Maputo provincial administration in settling the large number
of returning refugees.
</P>
<P>
Mathe said the South African authorities should have given a
note to the Mozambican government before hand, so that they could
get prepared for receiving the refugees who were kicked out by
South Africa as illegal residents.
</P>
<P>
Some of the counties bordering South Africa in Maputo Province
are hard hit by drought and it is difficult to send them back
there under this situation, Mathe said.
</P>
<P>
According to Mozambican News Agency, the South African
authorities have been repatriating hundreds of Mozambican
refugees each week via Ressano Garcia county alone.
</P>
<P>
It is said that there are several tens of thousands of
"illegally" Mozambicans living in South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
