<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethnic Groups Love Movies Dubbed in Their Own Languages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-eight-year-old farmer
Wei Shaofeng was excited recalling the first time he watched a
movie in which everyone spoke the language he speaks.
</P>
<P>
"The movie seemed to be shot in my village. I understood
everything," said Wei, who is from China's largest ethnic
group, the Zhuang nationality.
</P>
<P>
Baise Prefecture, in western Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region,
is a settlement of Zhuang people, and the place where late Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping staged an uprising and created the Seventh
Red Army in the 1920s.
</P>
<P>
Audiences were touched when they heard Deng Xiaoping speaking
the Zhuang language in the movie "Baise Uprising." Some watched
the film twice or more, and others walked tens of miles through
mountain paths to see the movie.
</P>
<P>
"We started to dub movies in the Zhuang language in 1958 when
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region was established," said Wei
Jiguang, an official in charge of ethnic-languages translations
for the Guangxi Film Company.
</P>
<P>
Projectionists acted as simultaneous translators at the
beginning to help audiences understand the plot.
</P>
<P>
"This action has been widely received by Zhuang and other
ethnic groups," said Wei Jiguang.
</P>
<P>
The Zhuang nationality, with a population of 15.43 million, is
the biggest ethnic group in China, and the Zhuang people are
mainly distributed over south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi now has nearly 100 translators working in nine cities
and counties, including the capital city of Nanning, and Baise,
Long'an and Jingxi. The translators work dubbing films into the
Zhuang, Miao, and Tong languages.
</P>
<P>
Beginning in 1985, the government of the autonomous region has
appropriated a special fund for dubbing. Over the past few years,
over 130 movies annually, on average, have been dubbed into ethnic
languages, attracting an audience of over four million viewers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
