<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 9 (Xinhua) -- China plans to invest 400
million yuan to construct or refurbish water conservation projects
in the lower reaches of the Yellow River, the nation's second
longest, between now and next spring.
</P>
<P>
The central government will allocate an additional 25.4 billion
yuan for water conservation projects throughout the nation. Close
to 18 percent of the funding will go for projects along the Yellow
River, with initial funding for this set at 655 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The total figure represents the largest sum of government
funding water conservation projects along the river since the
founding of new China, said Chen Xiaoguo, chief engineer with the
Yellow River Water Resources Committee.
</P>
<P>
Henan and Shandong provinces have formed a team of 100
hydrologists to preliminary designs for 17 key projects.  
