<HEADLINE> Trans-Regional Gas Pipeline Begins Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A new trans-regional gas
pipeline Thursday began transmitting gas from a major natural gas
field to Yinchuan, capital of Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The 293-km pipeline, which traverses Shaanxi, Inner Mongolia,
and Ningxia, is designed to transmit 400 million to 600 million
cubic meters of natural gas annually in its preliminary stage,
with capacity to be increased to one billion cubic meters in the
future.
</P>
<P>
The 470-million-yuan (about 56.62 million U.S. dollars)
facility, which is part of the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia Natural Gas
Field, is mainly designed to supply gas to a major fertilizer
facility in Yinchuan, as well as to local residents.
</P>
<P>
With verified reserves of 307.6 billion cubic meters, this
field is one of the largest onshore natural gas fields in the
world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
