<HEADLINE> EU, Euro Zone Unemployment Remain Stable in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment rates in both the
European Union (EU) and the euro zone remained stable in August,
Eurostat reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical bureau of the European
community said that the jobless rate for the 15-nation union was
10.0 percent while that for the 11-nation euro zone was 11.1
percent in August.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate for the EU a year ago was 10.6 percent
while the rate for the euro zone was 11.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Luxembourg still posted the lowest unemployment rate in both
the EU and the euro zone with 2.2 percent, followed by the
Netherlands at 3.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Spain, however, still had the highest jobless rate of 18.7
percent, despite the fact that it dropped slightly from 18.8
percent a month earlier.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat estimated that in August, a total of 16.8 million
persons were unemployed in the European Union and 14.1 million
people were jobless in the euro zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
