<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 15:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Slides Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market
continued sliding over the past week, mainly due to the price
retreat of banking stocks.
</P>
<P>
According to a weekly market review, issued Friday by Cyprus
Investment and Securities Corporation Limited (CISCO), the CISCO
All-Share Index closed on Thursday at 424.6, a 7.7 point decline
from last week.
</P>
<P>
"The main reason for this week's decline is the price retreat
of banking stocks, as the banking sector accounts for over 60
percent of total market capitalization," the review said.
</P>
<P>
Despite the losses of the past few weeks, the stock market's
capital appreciation is estimated at 9.1 percent since year end
1997. Taking into consideration the market's dividend yield for
the same period which is preliminary estimated at 4.3 percent, the
total stock market return so far within 1998 rises to 13.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Overall, the mild downtrend that captured the market since the
end of August appears to be reinforced, the review said, adding
that in the absence of further economic developments and in the
light of the current deadlock in the political front of island's
peace process, the stock market does not seem braced up for any
decisive upswing.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of transactions this week was 5.6 million
Cyprus pounds (about 11.2 million U.S. dollars), compared to 4.9
million pounds (about 9.8 million dollars) the week before.
</P>
</TEXT>
