<HEADLINE> Bronze Statue Memorializes Late Chinese President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held today in the
Chinese capital to unveil bronze statues memorizing Liu Shaoqi, a
late Chinese state president.
</P>
<P>
liu was also called a great proletarian revolutionary,
statesman, theorist and a late senior leader of the ruling
Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Wan Guoquan, vice chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference( CPPCC), and
Wang Guangmei, Liu's widow, attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Liu was born in Ningxiang County, Hunan Province, on November
24, 1898. He served as the president of China in the late 1950s
and early 1960s. Liu was widely respected as a "public servant who
served the people" and contributed to China's revolution and
modernization.
</P>
<P>
Three statues, which each stand 13 centimeters in height and
weigh 800 grams, will be in the Museum of Chinese Revolution, Liu
Shaoqi Memorial Hall and for Wang Guangmei herself.  
</P>
</TEXT>
