<HEADLINE> Zoff Ready for Italy's Swiss Clash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Dino Zoff returned to his city of
birth -- Udine -- on Saturday to throw Italy's young bloods into
a "local derby" European championship qualifier against
Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The Italy coach started his career with local side Udinese in
the early 1960s before moving on to bigger things with Napoli,
Juventus and the Italian national side, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The decision to play the match in Udine was taken in Zoff's
honor. The tie is his first in charge on Italian soil following
his debut as coach in Italy's 2-0 defeat of Wales last month.
</P>
<P>
Following are the possible teams:
</P>
<P>
Italy - Gianluigi Buffon; Paolo Maldini (captain), Fabio
Cannavaro, Christian Panucci, Gianluca Pessotto, Dino Baggio,
Luigi Di Biagio or Demetrio Albertini, Diego Fuser, Eusebio Di
Francesco; Filippo Inzaghi, Alessandro Del Piero or Francesco
Totti.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland:
</P>
<P>
