<DOCNO> XIE19981009.0120 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 13:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hardliner Sharon Named Israeli Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu Friday named Ariel Sharon, a prominent
hardliner in the cabinet, as the foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
In a news conference hold in Prime Minister Office in
Jerusalem, Netanyahu said that Sharon will take the portfolio of
foreign minister next Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sharon will continue to be the minister of national
infrastructure for another three months.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu said that the appointment of Sharon is completely
in line with "our desire" for peace.
</P>
<P>
Sharon is considered an influential figure in Israeli politics as
he enjoys wide support among hardliners in the Jewish country.
He has been opposing to making compromise in the negotiations with
the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
He is also the member of Netanyahu's "kitchen cabinet,"
which also includes Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordecai and Trade
Minister Natan Sharansky.
</P>
<P>
The "kitchen cabinet" is responsible to make crucial decisions
on the peace negotiations with the Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Sharon, an former general in the army, is also
recognized as a war hero in Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio said earlier on Friday that Netanyahu has informed
the U.S. and Palestinian officials that he plans to name Sharon as
foreign minister during the visit of the U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright to the region early this week.
</P>
<P>
Sharon is reportedly to be in charge of the negotiations with
the Palestinians in the final-status talks. And his appointment
would ease the opposition of the right-wing in Netanyahu's
government against signing peace agreements with the
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sharon is expected to travel with Netanyahu to
Washington next week, attending the three-way summit meeting of
the U.S., Israeli and Palestinian leaders.
</P>
<P>
The summit, which will be hosted by U.S. President Bill
Clinton, is hoped to wrap up an agreement on the long-delayed
Israeli troops' second redeployment in the West Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981009.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. to Provide Aid to Lesotho: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations will
provide emergency humanitarian and relief assistance to Lesotho,
South African Press Association quoted a U.N. official as saying
Friday in Maseru, the capital of Lesotho.
</P>
<P>
The.U.N Development Program (UNDP) would organize an
assessment to determine the needs of those worst hit by the
upheavals after a Southern African Development Community (SADC)
military intervention late in September, U.N. resident
coordinator Edward Omotoso said.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP would also launch a program to assist and facilitate
the implementation of any agreement eventually reached by the
political parties in Lesotho.
</P>
<P>
The assistance follows recent disturbance in which heavy
losses were inflicted during the Lesotho turmoil which was
resulted from allegation that the May 23 general election was
rigged in favor of the government.
</P>
<P>
Omotoso said the Lesotho crisis had debilitated the health
system's ability to deliver care to the large numbers of
casualties.
</P>
<P>
Lesotho's main hospital, Queen Elizabeth II in Maseru, was
reportedly forced to transfer patients requiring blood
transfusions to Bloemfontein, South Africa, because the
hopsital's HIV blood testing device had broken down.
</P>
<P>
The World Health Organizatio will provide emergency relief
at Queen Elizabeth II Hospital and at St. Joseph Hospital. It
will also supply surgical equipment and assist in monitoring the
outbreak of contagious diseases in riot-hit Maseru and other
parts of the kingdom.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. World Food Program would provide emergency food aid
by mobilizing international donors and would also assist the
Lesotho government to identify its need for goods, Omotoso added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981009.0122 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CCTV Celebrates 40th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Vice Premier Li Lanqing attended
today's celebrations marking the 40th anniversary of China Central
Television (CCTV), the hallmark of China's television industry.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, and Li Ruihuan penned
inscriptions for the the event. President Jiang Zemin
wrote: "Playing an important role in the television media in a
better way, and serving reform, opening up and socialist
modernization".
</P>
<P>
An inscription by Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee
of National People's Congress (NPC), reads: "Building CCTV into a
bridge linking China with the rest of the world".
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji toured CCTV facilities on Wednesday and
extended congratulations to CCTV and TV industry on their 40th
anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), penned an
inscription which reads: "Keeping the audience in mind at all
times."
</P>
<P>
Li Lanqing expressed warm congratulations to the television
industry and CCTV staffers on behalf of the Central Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
CCTV and television stations at all levels represent an
important media airing public opinion and have played an extremely
important role of media supervision, Li said, adding that
people working in the industry shoulder responsibilities for
contributing to the reform and opening up effort, safeguarding the
stability and unity of the nation, and promoting the socialist
material and ethic and cultural progress to a new plateau.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that the television sector should strictly adhere
to guiding the public opinion, expand reforms, improve reportage
and train professional staffers.
</P>
<P>
Li called on all the people working in the country's TV
industry to rally more closely around the CPC Central Committee
with Jiang Zemin at the core, hold high the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory, work hard and dare to blaze new trails and make
fresh contributions to the continuous development and prosperity
of China's TV industry.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, head of the Publicity Department of the CPC
Central Committee, was among the senior officials attending the
celebrations.
</P>
<P>
CCTV's eight channels offer 160 hours of daily programming
which reaches 98 percent of countries and regions across the
world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
