<HEADLINE> Philippine President to Visit Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Ejercito Estrada will pay a state visit to Singapore from October
11 to 14 at the invitation of his Singapore counterpart Ong Teng
Cheong, Singapore Ministry of Foreign Affairs announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
The visit will be the first trip abroad by Estrada since he
assumed presidency at the end of June.
</P>
<P>
During his visit , Estrada will call on Singapore President Ong
Teng Cheong and meet with Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong
for talks on a range of issues including their bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine president will also meet separately with local
Filipino community and prominent representatives of the Singapore
private sector at a business luncheon.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Estrada will deliver a keynote speech at the
Seventh East Asia Economic Summit organized by the
Switzerland-based World Economic Forum in partnership with the
Singapore Economic Development Board. The summit, with the theme
"Pushing Ahead with Responses to the Crisis; Shaping the New
Economic Landscape in Asia", is due to be held from October 12 to
14 with an expected throng of about 1,000 participants among whom
Estrada is the sole head of state. 
</P>
