<HEADLINE> Seoul Share Price Up 7.45 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The composite stock price index in
Seoul stock market Friday soared up 7.45 percent, or 22.74 points,
closing at 327.96 due to falling interest rate and rosy prospects
for export following the Japanese yen's rally against the
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume surged to 113.29 million shares on a turnover of
627.1 billion won ( 471.5 million U.S. dollars). Friday's rise
is the third biggest gain this year after a 8.5 percent reap on
June 17 and a 7.65 percent increase on January 30.
</P>
<P>
Winner outnumbered losers at 625 to 141 while 92 shares remained
unchanged. Foreign investors were selling shares worth 64.1 billion
won (46.5 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in the foreign exchange currency market here,
Friday's exchange rate of the won to the greenback ended at 1,330,
up from Thursday's 1,361 won.
</P>
<P>
The value of Japanese yen also enjoyed a continuous rise with
the exchange rate of 115-116 yen against one dollar on the Tokyo
market Friday. A stronger yen is widely seen to reduce South
Korean import from Japan while making South Korean exports more
competitive in overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
Stock analysts said the yen's appreciation nearly eclipsed the
recent anxieties over a global economic downturn and the current
crisis in South Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
