<HEADLINE> Bank to Offer Automobile Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank
(CCB) has begun offering automobile loans at its Beijing, Shanghai
and Guangzhou branches with ratification from the People's Bank of
China, the first time a state-owned commercial bank has offered
such service.
</P>
<P>
A CCB spokesman said these new loans are expected to expand
effectively market demand, to some extent reverse the declining
trend of national industrial production, and ultimately energize
efforts to reach this year's goal of eight percent economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Since China implemented opening and reform policies in the late
1970s, its automobile industry has developed rapidly with design,
performance and production scale greatly improved. However, due to
inadequate banking services, the automobile market is short of
effective demand, and auto producers are suffering from increased
stock and delayed payment.
</P>
<P>
The bank launched its automobile loans on the basis of
extensive market investigation and feasibility studies, the
spokesman noted.
</P>
<P>
The CCB has auto loan experience in offering such loans to taxi
companies, the spokesman said. The bank's extensive business
network in large and medium-sized cities will help the development
of automobile loans.  
</P>
