<HEADLINE> Cape Verde Has New Chief of Staff: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- President of the Republic of
Cape Verde Friday appointed Lt. Col. Jorge Bittencourt Pinto as
the chief of staff of the armed forces in the island country,
according to a press report reaching here from Praia.
</P>
<P>
Pinto has succeeded Col. Amilcar Baptista whose term would
have ended in February next year according to the law of Cape
Verde, said the report from the capital of the African country.
</P>
<P>
President Monteiro demanded that Baptista should resign
because the president was not happy with the appointment of the
commander of the Sao Vincente Command Area by the former chief of
staff in mid-September, it said.
</P>
<P>
Military sources in Cape Verde said that the appointment of
Pinto as the chief of staff will lead to a major restructuring in
the services of the armed forces in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
