<HEADLINE> Macao Banker Appeals to Taiwan for Reunification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A celebrated Macao businessman
said here Friday morning that Taiwan authorities should value the
righteous cause of the Chinese nation and hold cross-Straits
political talks as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have shown that cooperation (between the Communist and
Kuomintang parties) benefits the country, while separation sap its
vitality," said Ho Hau Wah, general manager of the Tai Fung Bank of
Macao and chairman of the Macao Bankers Association.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a gathering marking the 87th anniversary
of the Revolution of 1911 which overthrew thousands of years of
feudal monarchy and paved the way for democratic revolution in
modern China.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Sun Yat-sen, leader of the revolution and founder of the
Kuomintang Party, joined hands with the Communist Party in the
1920s to fight against reactionary warlords.
</P>
<P>
Ho Hau Wah acknowledged that cooperation between the two
parties made significant contributions to the Chinese nation,
adding that the reunification of China is the common wish of the
people across the Taiwan Straits, and is a major trend which no
one can resist.
</P>
<P>
The banker expressed his hope that the Taiwan authorities will
make concerted efforts with the mainland to revitalize the Chinese
nation, build a reunified and prosperous China, and contribute
still more to the peace and progress of the mankind.
</P>
<P>
"The smooth return of Hong Kong (to the motherland) and Macao's
upcoming return will surely provide favorable examples and
facilitate the resolution of the Taiwan question," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ho Hau Wah pointed out that Sun Yat-sen was a great and
patriotic figure who was in opposition to the disintegration of
the country.
</P>
<P>
Scores of people from all walks of life in Macao took part in
the gathering at the Kiang Wu Hospital, where Dr. Sun Yat-sen once
worked. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
