<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 7.15 Percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks surged
sharply to a higher close Friday with hopes of an imminent
interest rate cut.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index gained 567.28 points, or 7.15 percent, to
close at 8,506.79 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This is the third consecutive growth for the benchmark index
this week and it takes two and a half months for the index to
reach 8,500 points again after July 21 this year.
</P>
<P>
The Property shares took a lead in the overall growth in the
stock market, with the share prices leapt 906.26 points, or 9.80
percent, to close at 10,155.12. The Property share prices have
climbed 22.32 percent in three days.
</P>
<P>
Prices for shares of Commercial and Industry, Finance and
Utilities advanced by 8.24 percent, 7.87 percent and 4.15 percent
respectively on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Friday's turnover amounted to 9.126 billion HK dollars (1.17
billion U.S. dollars), 3.291 billion HK dollars (422 million U.S.
dollars) more than that in the previous trading day.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the hope for an interest rate cut, the active
buying on the stocks was mainly boosted the stronger Japanese yen
and lower local interbank rates.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index rose 86.66 points, or 1.09 percent, to open
at 8,026.17 Friday morning. It was 285.85 points, or 3.60 percent,
up when the market closed at lunchbreak.
</P>
<P>
The share prices rose 194.79 points, or 2.52 percent, to close
at 7,939.51 on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
