<HEADLINE> Moderate Air Pollution in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- China's capital Beijing, and
Zhengzhou, capital of central Henan Province, suffered from
moderate air pollution during the past week, according to the
China Environmental Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
The center's latest air-quality report said that the major
problem in Beijing was nitrogen oxide, while Zhengzhou reported
high levels of suspended particles during the October 2-8 period.
</P>
<P>
The cities of Tianjin, Xi'an, Lanzhou, Shenyang, Chongqing and
Guangzhou suffered from slight air pollution during the period,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
The major problem in Guangzhou was nitrogen oxide, and Chongqing
suffered from sulphur dioxide. Other cities all reported high
levels of suspended particles.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the weather in northern China over the past
week was mainly overcast with low wind speeds, conditions
unfavorable to dispersing air pollutants.
</P>
<P>
However, twenty-five cities in southern China reported good air
quality, including Shanghai, Kunming, Chengdu, Nanjing and Guilin.
</P>
<P>
Seven cities -- Shantou, Beihai, Zhanjiang, Ningbo, Xiamen,
Shenzhen and Haikou -- enjoyed excellent air quality during the
period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
