<HEADLINE> Tourists in Groups to Macao Upsurge in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The number of tourists to Macao
via travel agencies rose markedly in August this year, but the
number from January to August slumped, according to the latest
figures issued by the Macao Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
Tourist arrivals to Macao in groups reached 86,722 in August,
an increase of 41.8 percent over the same month last year. And
those from the inland areas of China, Taiwan and Japan accounted
for 88 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
However, Macao saw the influx of 585,538 persons of group
tourists during the first eight months of the year. The figure was
18.7 percent less than that in the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in August 15,373 Macao residents went outside for
tour with the assistance of travel agencies, an increase of 48.3
percent over the same month of 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
