erupted again Friday in the West Bank town of Hebron, where
a Jordanian visitor was killed and several Palestinians were
injured in clashes Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Tension has been mounting in the West Bank since Israel
sealed off the areas and the Gaza Strip last month following
the killing of two members of the Islamic militant group Hamas
by Israeli troops.
</P>
<P>
Hamas has repeated its threat to attack Israelis for
retaliation, including committing suicide bombings and kidnaping
hitchhiking Israeli soldiers. 
