<HEADLINE> Malaysian Mission Seeking Europe Joint Venture Opportunities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will send a trade
and investment mission later this month to Switzerland, France,
the Netherlands and Germany to seek joint venture opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The mission to the European countries from October 15 to 21
will be led by International Trade and Industry Minister Rafidah
Aziz and will comprise five government officials from four states
and 25 private sector members representing 21 companies, the
International Trade and Industry Ministry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The mission plans, among others, to inform Europe corporations
of the investment opportunities in Malaysia and to update and
brief the European business community on the economic situation in
Malaysia and policy measures taken by the Malaysian government,
the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The mission will seek joint venture opportunities in oil and
gas, motor vehicles refurbishment/reconditioning, wood-based
industries, agro-based industries, manufacturing of medical
disposal products, telemedicine and information technology,
petro-chemical and shipbuilding.
</P>
<P>
The mission will also provide opportunities for Malaysian
corporate representatives to have a business meeting with the
business community in Zurich, Paris, Amsterdam and Stuttgart for
joint business collaborations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
