will hold talks with Turkish officials to continue his mediation.
</P>
<P>
Iran is the current chairman of the Organization of Islamic
Conference which embraces Syria and Turkey as members.
</P>
<P>
The current tension between Syria and Turkey erupted early this
month, with Turkey accusing Syria of harboring militants of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in its territory, but the
Syrian side categorically denied the charges.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has been massing troops along its border with Syria and
threatened to use force to uproot those alleged military training
camps of the PKK inside Syria if Syria does not stop supporting
the Kurdish rebels in 45 days.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting for an independent Kurdistan in
southeastern Turkey in the last 14 years. 
</P>
