<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rally on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rallied for a
third day on Singapore Stock Market Friday boosted by the strong
Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) soared 25.69 points to
976.65 points in active dealings.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover shot up to 342.37 million units valued at
430.55 million Singapore dollars (261.18 million U.S. dollars).
Advancers outnumbered decliners by 214 to 34 with 172 counters
unchanged..
</P>
<P>
PSL was the most active stock of the day as it had a volume of
57.01 million units traded. KepLand was again the second most
heavily traded stock with a volume of 29.02 million units. TAC 200
was next with 15.25 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
DBS F led the ascent of the day with a rise of 60 cents to 8.10
 Singapore dollars at close. UOB moved up 46 cents to end at 4.00
Singapore dollars. Aetro was up 43 cents to close at 1.29
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SIA F was the biggest loser of the day as it
lost 40 cents to close at 9.00 Singapore dollars. YHS was the
second biggest loser of the day with a slide of 24 cents to 3.26
Singapore dollars. SuperCof w01 shed off 22 cents to end at 0.08
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market was boosted by the strong Japanese yen.
The yen's ability to hold on to gains on the U.S. dollar renewed
interest in Singapore blue chips, they added.
</P>
<P>
they also noted that some small stocks also rose on a more
bullish Asian currency market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
