<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Prepares for La Nina-Caused Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada has ordered four government agencies to lead stepped-up
preparations for expected heavy rains and flash floods caused by
La Nina weather disturbance, a presidential press release said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The press release said the president issued the directive to
the departments of national defense, agriculture, health, and
social welfare and development.
</P>
<P>
"All departments are ready. The four will be the leading
agencies to prepare for La Nina, which I still hope will no longer
come," the president was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Estrada ordered the Department of Social Welfare and
Development to clean up waterways in provinces that could be
affected by heavy rains with the help of military engineers in
these areas.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Defense Secretary Orlando Mercado reported that
the military has pre-positioned equipment such as vessels and
rubber boats from the Navy and Air Force.
</P>
<P>
"Our Navy, Air Force and Army have already conducted rehearsals
and in fact, they are continuing their coordination, and even the
reserve force has pitched in," Mercado was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Estrada ordered the Health Department to send
doctors to disaster areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
