<HEADLINE> ACJA Urges Protecting Rights of Journalists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Journalists
Association (ACJA) on Thursday called for respecting and
protecting the rights of journalists to report.
</P>
<P>
The association stressed that the Party and the people depend
on journalists to provide a voice to ensure correct public
supervision.
</P>
<P>
An ACJA committee for guaranteeing the legitimate rights and
interests of journalists sent telegrams to the association's
subordinate units in northeastern China's Heilongjiang Province
expressing support for Xiao Zhizhuo, a female journalist who was
viciously attacked while conducting a recent interview on an
unauthorized construction project.
</P>
<P>
Xiao, a reporter for the Heilongjiang Daily, was dispatched on
Monday to report on alleged illegal construction at No.113 Angu
Street in the provincial capital of Harbin. The property owner
responded with verbal abuse. Xiao's glasses were broken and she
sustained an injury to her right eye in an ensuing melee involving
construction workers.
</P>
<P>
The ACJA urged concerned departments in Heilongjiang to
expedite the investigation of the incident and render appropriate
punishment to those involved. The association also called on the
general public to support and assist journalists attempting to
cover the news. 
</P>
</TEXT>
