<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-French Organizations Expand Regional Cooperation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- China and France strengthened
links between local organizations in the two nations earlier this
week when the Nord-Pas de Calais Region in the latter opened a
Beijing representative office.
</P>
<P>
French Ambassador to China Pierre Morel attended the opening
ceremony on Thursday and said the establishment of the office
represents a major step in implementing the partnership between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
French President Jacques Chirac visited China last year and
leaders of the two nations agreed to expand cooperation between
local governments and organizations.
</P>
<P>
Nord-Pas de Calais became the first local French region to open
a representative office in Beijing following last month's visit by
French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin. The Regional Development
Agency (RDA) of Nord-Pas de Calais will operate the office.
</P>
<P>
The Channel Tunnel links the region, one of France's major
transportation hubs and industrial areas, with England. Nord-Pas
de Calais accounts for 30 percent of the country's textile
production and 13 percent of total foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Morel said that increasing cooperation between local regions is
a rapidly expanding aspect of Sino-French relations.
</P>
<P>
Three other French regions have also set up long-term
cooperative ties with cities and provinces in China, including
ties between Rhone Alps and Shanghai, Bretagne and Jinan in east
China's Shandong Province, and Toulouse and Chongqing Municipality
in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the government should not be the sole player in
enhancing Sino-French relations. He stressed that governments at
various levels, organizations and individuals must join forces to
expand cooperation in all fields, including culture, trade,
finance and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The regional council founded the RDA in 1984 as part of an
effort to create favorable conditions for the region's economic
development.
</P>
<P>
RDA President Christian Bataille said the representative office
in Beijing will promote China business opportunities for French
companies, especially small and medium-sized enterprises. The
agency will provide information, consulting to help reduce risks
facing small enterprises entering the vast Chinese market. The RDA
will also help French companies find cooperative partners.
</P>
</TEXT>
