<HEADLINE> Incompetent College Teachers Laid-off in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 9 (Xinhua) -- South China University of
Science and Technology has removed 65 professors from their
positions for poor teaching performance.
</P>
<P>
These professors, part of a staff of 328 tutors for
postgraduates, recently had their teaching and research abilities
appraised.
</P>
<P>
The university, based in Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province, is one of the province's pilot universities
for introducing competitiveness into their personnel management.
</P>
<P>
This marks a big step forward in the province's reform of the
personnel system in institutions of higher learning.
</P>
<P>
In the past, most teachers at these institutions did not have
to worry about being discharged, for school authorities never
fired any teacher.
</P>
<P>
The situation is quite different today.
</P>
<P>
The province's Zhongshan Medical Sciences University has also
introduced reform into its employment system by dividing teachers
into three classes -- excellent, good and poor -- according to
their performance.
</P>
<P>
According to provincial authorities, the reform aims to
improve faculty quality in universities and raise overall
teaching standards.  
</P>
</TEXT>
