<HEADLINE> Sino-Jamaican Friendship Hailed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
met here today with visiting Jamaican Prime Minister Percival
Patterson and said that the two countries should usher in the next
century with long-term, sustained and stable Sino-Jamaican
relations.
</P>
<P>
By so doing, President Jiang added, the two countries will
continue to support each other and expand the scope of their
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said that there is no conflict of
interest between China and Jamaica. On the contrary, both
countries are confronted with the same tasks of advancing their
economies and enhancing the standards of living of their peoples,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciations for the Jamaican government's
adherence to the "one China" stand, and gave thanks for its
support of China on the issues of Taiwan and human rights.
</P>
<P>
Since the two countries forged diplomatic ties 26 years ago,
substantial achievements have been scored in bilateral cooperation
in the fields of politics, economy, culture and other fields,
Jiang said, adding that the two countries shared views on many
international issues.
</P>
<P>
Jiang praised the Jamaican government for its efforts to
safeguard national sovereignty, rejuvenate its economy, and
increase the standard of living for its people.
</P>
<P>
He cited Jamaica as a major Caribbean nation, saying that it is
playing a more important role in international and regional
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also said that although China has suffered some of the
worst flooding in history, this will not hinder his country in
meeting its economic growth goal, and the reforms and opening-up
have not been stalled.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Patterson said that his current visit is aimed
at consolidating existing Jamaican-Chinese friendship.
</P>
<P>
He said that at the turn of the century, strengthening
bilateral ties will not only bring benefit to the people of the
two countries, but will also be conductive to the peace and
stability of the world.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Patterson spoke highly of China's great economic
achievements, and called the country a stablizing factor in the
Asia-Pacific region and in the world at large. 
</P>
</TEXT>
