<HEADLINE> China Exports 100 Aircraft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- China has exported 100 airplanes
of various models to more than 20 countries and regions in Asia,
Africa, Oceania and South America, with a combined transaction
value of more than 300 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The exports include the Yun-7 and Yun-8, and Yun-12
airliners, according to the China Aero-Technology Import and
Export Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The Yun-12 plane has been sought after by importers for its
high quality, reliable functioning, and low price. British and
U.S. aviation administrations have given airworthiness
certificates to this model, which can be widely used for
air-drops, agriculture, forestry, geological prospecting and
sightseeing, the corporation said.
</P>
<P>
China has set the goal of independently developing large
airliners through co-production with the world's leading
airplane manufacturers, a source said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
