<HEADLINE> Shanghai Fixed Assets Investment Up 0.6 Percent in Eight Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai invested 80.8 billion
yuan in fixed assets expansion in the first eight months of the
year, up 0.6 percent over the same period last year, the city's
statistics bureau reported today.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said that investment in the city's infrastructure
witnessed the biggest growth rate of 50.8 percent, adding that
"big chunks of money were invested for an airport in the Pudong
New Area, a ring road and the second subway line."
</P>
<P>
It said August saw explosive growth rates for investment in
capital construction, which grew 68 percent over last year to
about 74 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Pudong New Area, an economic development zone erected on
farmland on the east side of the Huangpu River seven years ago,
had a drastic increase in fixed assets investment in August.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4.7 billion yuan, or a 61.8-percent increase on an
annual basis, was invested in fixed assets in Pudong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
