<HEADLINE> Preparations for '98 China Air Show Near Completion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Construction of an exhibition
center and related basic facilities for the '98 China
International Air Show in Zhuhai, south China's Guangdong
Province, have been almost completed, an official of the Civil
Aviation Administration of China (CAAC) said here today.
</P>
<P>
The city, which will host the air show between November 15-22,
has invested one billion yuan (120.48 million U.S. dollars) to
build an 23-km eight-lane highway around the local airport, a
press center covering 8,000 sq.m. and a number of hotels and
conference centers.
</P>
<P>
The parking apron is to be expanded to 500,000 sq.m. to
accommodate 200 aircraft, while a special exhibition area of
50,000 square meters will be ready for the show.
</P>
<P>
Over 860 domestic and foreign companies from 28 countries and
regions will participate in the event, which will feature 120
aircraft and a number of special performances.
</P>
<P>
According to the CAAC official, about one billion people are
expected to view the show on TV, apart from some one million
people present at the show which will be covered by over 2,500
journalists.
</P>
<P>
Space products will also be exhibited in a special hall
covering 3,000 sq.m., with two Long Market rockets on display in a
4,000-sq.m. outdoor exhibition area.
</P>
<P>
The show, the largest of its kind in China, is held every two
years. The first show took place in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
