<HEADLINE> Dhaka Decides to Phase out Polybags in Five Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
decided to phase out production of polybags and ultimately ban its
use for keeping the environment safe.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at an inter-ministerial meeting held here
Thursday, which discussed ways and means to eliminate polybags
used in large scale across the country, English newspapers here
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting recommended complete ban of polybags in five years
under a five-year action, which includes massive of collection of
polybags in the city, discouraging import of raw materials by
imposing high duties on it, encouraging uses of jute bags or other
cheaper devises and scaling down both demand and supply of
polythene in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
