<HEADLINE> U.S. Heavyweight Champ Accused Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 8 (Xinhua) -- U.S. former heavyweight
champion Michael Dokes Pleaded innocent Thursday in a Las Vegas
court after being accused of attempted murder in the beating of
his fiancee.
</P>
<P>
Dokes was arrested on August 31 after his fiancee went to a
hospital for treatment of injuries. She told police she was
beaten, sexually assaulted and held against her will by Dokes.
</P>
<P>
The victim suffered several facial fractures and was so
severely beaten that her face was unrecognizable, police said.
</P>
<P>
Dokes was charged with attempted murder, sexual assault and
false imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
Dokes held the WBA heavyweight title in 1982 briefly, but his
career was ruined by drug arrests and cocaine abuse. He made a
comeback and fought for the heavyweight title in 1993, but was
stopped by Riddick Bowe in the first round. 
