<DOCNO> XIE19981009.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai National Team Members Face Doping Testing Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Games doping control
test committee will test athletes from 10 sports, and those found
positive could be sacked from the Thai national team.
</P>
<P>
Doctor Varin Tanthasuppasiri, in charge of the Games doping
control, said his team would start tests this month by examining
samples of athletes' urine from athletics, boxing, cycling, sepak
takraw, shooting, swimming, weightlifting, windsurfing, rugby
football and wrestling, the Nation newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
"We will focus on steroids and other prohibited substances. We
will be especially concerned for certain sports such as boxing,
wrestling and weightlifting as athletes tend to depend on banned
substances," said Varin.
</P>
<P>
The committee will select only 50 urine samples, which will be
sent to the official doping control center of the Asian Games at
Mahidol University. The 13th Asian Games will be held in Thailand
in December.
</P>
<P>
"If any athlete tests positive, I will submit the name to the
Olympic Committee of Thailand to decide on the punishment.
</P>
<P>
"They could even end up being deleted from the national team
list," he said.
</P>
<P>
Varin also said he had to begin the test in October because
steroids become effective when injected six to eight weeks before
a competition.
</P>
<P>
"However it is possible that some athletes might use some
substances to clear the steroid in their urine not long before a
competition. So we have to be very careful about this case too,"
Varin added.
</P>
<P>
Medically, the use of steroid can be very hazardous to the
body, but negative effects will not be immediately obvious but
occur especially at between 30 and 40 years, after most athletes
have retired from competition.
</P>
<P>
"The accumulation of steroids in the body can cause high blood
pressure, fat in blood vessels, liver cancer and heart attacks.
You need a lot of money to cure these sicknesses, and sometimes
you must be under medical supervision for the rest of your life,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
"So it is not worth using these banned substances just to
become famous or successful in a competition. I would like Thai
athletes to be aware of the negative aspects of using steroids,"
the doctor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
