<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A senior Bulgarian official said
Thursday that his country will not take part in any possible
military strikes on Yugoslavia "for the time being" over the
Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after a meeting of the parliamentary
Foreign Policy Committee, Committee Chairman Assen Agov said that
the Bulgarian parliament is ready to react depending on the
developments in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
