<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Amidst reports of sighting of
unidentified aircraft over the Northern theater of operations, the
Sri Lankan Air Force has further increased anti-aircraft defenses.
</P>
<P>
Air Force sources Friday said they had taken the claims of
sighting aircraft and helicopters seriously.
</P>
<P>
Defenses in Colombo and other areas threatened by possible
Tamil terrorist air attacks had been provided increased security,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
In the last few months detection of unidentified echoes by
Naval vessels operating in the Northern waters fueled speculation
that the Tamil rebels had acquired a helicopter, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
According to military sources, the rebels could have acquired
small aircraft which can be smuggled in a knocked-down condition,
said the sources, adding that they ruled out the possibility of
the rebels producing their own aircraft. But they could build a
mission for a single suicide attack.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and east
of the country. 
