<HEADLINE> Earthquake Hits Southern Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake shook
southern Peru Wednesday night, causing no deaths and injuries,
Peru's Geophysics Institute reported.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was 44 kilometers northwest of Arequipa, Peru's
second largest city, located 750 kilometers southeast of Lima.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake, measuring 5.3 degrees on the Richter scale,
occurred 55 kilometers beneath the earth's surface, it said.
</P>
<P>
The quake caused walls to collapse in shantytowns and people to
flee their homes. 
</P>
