<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Unemployment to Hit 20 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's unemployment will
reach 20 million this year, about 22 percent of the country's
estimated 90 million workforce, the Indonesian Observer Friday
quoted a minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
"At the moment the unemployment figure is 18 million but
through to the end of 1998 the figure is estimated to reach 20
million," Manpower Minister Fahmi Idris said.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with President B.J. Habibie on Thursday, Idris
said unemployment could stabilize at this level in 1999, depending
on how the economy developed and whether the rupiah continues to
strengthen against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The government would continue with job creation schemes,
including irrigation and road projects, to try to keep
unemployment down, he said.
</P>
<P>
The government would also approach foreign countries,
particularly in the Middle East, to see if they could take more
skilled Indonesian workers, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
