<HEADLINE> Northeastern China Reports Steady Growth in Private Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Province, an old
industrial base in northeastern China, reported a 47-percent
growth in the GDP of the private sector to 30.88 billion yuan
from January to June this year.
</P>
<P>
About 2.54 million people were employed in the private sector
by the end of June, 320,000 people more than a year ago. The
province now has 255 private businesses each with a capital of 10
million yuan, including 146 conglomerates. From January to June,
the total capital of the private sector amounted to 41.8 billion
yuan, up 97.2 percent from last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
The efficiency of private enterprises has also been
improving. They had 34.45 billion yuan in output value and 92.95
billion yuan in earnings in the six months to June, up 28 percent
and 70 percent respectively from the same period of 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
