<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Makes Dramatic Comeback From </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks Thursday
made a dramatic comeback from their heavy losses after bargain
hunters stepped in to staunch the frenzied selling.
</P>
<P>
Based on early, unofficial data, the Dow Jones industrial
average ended off 9.78 points, or 0.13 percent, at 7,731.91 after
shaking off a loss of nearly 275 points in the earlier afternoon.
</P>
<P>
In the broader market, declines swamped advances by a huge 5 to
1 margin on very heavy volume of 1.11 billion shares on the New
York Stock Exchange. Technology, Internet and financial stocks
suffered some of the biggest losses.
</P>
<P>
Amid a frenzy selling caused by this week's sudden nose dive by
the U.S. dollar in currency trading, the Dow industrials fell
nearly 275 points in earlier tradings Thursday. The dollar
reportedly fell sharply Thursday after sliding 8.1 percent
Wednesday against the Japanese yen, the biggest one-day drop in a
quarter century.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed the Dow's recovery to investors who were
dismissing the day's jitters and instead looking for cheap stocks.
</P>
</TEXT>
