<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100GMT, October 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- The U.N. Secretary General's special envoy on Afghan
affairs Lakhdar Brahimi stated here on Thursday that no peace
would exist in Afghanistan without establishment of a broad-based
government.
</P>
<P>
Brahimi made the remark at a press conference while answering
Xinhua correspondent's question about the possibility to establish
a broad-based government in Afghanistan after the Afghan Taliban
militia occupied more than 90 percent the country's territory.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the international community would work for the
benefit of the Afghan people, "so, the first thing is to stop the
human rights abuses in Afghanistan." (BC-Iran-Brahimi-Afghanistan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian troops clashed with the Afghan Taliban
militia Thursday on Iran's northeastern border area, Iranian
television reported.
</P>
<P>
Taliban militants raided Iranian border posts in northeastern
Khorasan province early Thursday and Iranian border guards
returned fire, repulsing the attackers, the report said.
(BC-Iran-Taliban-Clash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Visiting U.S. Assistant Secretary of State Martin
Indyk said here Thursday that Washington will begin its mediation
to defuse the Turkish-Syrian crisis.
</P>
<P>
Emerging from talks with Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa,
Indyk said Washington will exert efforts to "strike a compromise
between toning down the tension and taking into account the
Turkish apprehensions." (BC-Egypt-US-Turkey)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- Syrian President Hafez al-Assad Thursday welcomed
the Iranian initiative for mediation of Syria-Turkey tension,
calling for dialog to settle the dispute.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with al-Assad Thursday afternoon, visiting Iranian
Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi handed over a message from Iranian
President Mohammad Khatami to al-Assad which addressed the
Syria-Turkey tension and Iran's efforts to contain it, said Syrian
presidential spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Al-Assad and Kharrazi discussed the ways of enabling the dialog
to dominate in settling the disputable issues, the spokesman added.
(BC-Syria-Turkey-Iran)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A Palestinian was killed on Thursday during the
clashes between Palestinian protesters and Israeli soldiers in
the West Bank city of Hebron, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The clashes erupted as dozens of Palestinians threw stones at
Israeli soldiers guarding Jewish enclaves in the
Israeli-controlled downtown sector of Hebron. And the soldiers
responded with rubber-coated bullets.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Palestinian youth was hit on the head by a
rubber bullet and died in a hospital.
</P>
<P>
A number of other Palestinians were injured in the clashes,
including a cameraman who was working for the Agence France-Presse
news agency. (Hebron-Clash-Palestinian Killed) 
</P>
