<HEADLINE> Ivanov Says Contact Group Closer to Solution on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov said Thursday that the Contact Group on former Yugoslavia
was moving closer to reaching a political settlement on Kosovo
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference after a special Contact Group
meeting in London Thursday, Ivanov said: "I am deeply convinced
that we moved closer today to a political settlement of the
(Kosovo) question."
</P>
<P>
Ivanov, who briefed members of the six-nation Contact Group on
his talks with Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic reaffirmed
his country's strong oppsition to any military intervention in
Kosovo by saying: "Russia's position on the use of force is clear
and has not changed."
</P>
<P>
"Only the (UN) Security Council has the right to take any
decision on the use of force," Ivanov said, adding: "bypassing it
in this way not only would not contribute to solving the Kosovo
problem, but would have dire consequences of an international
nature".
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers from United States, Britain, France, Germany,
Italy and Russia attended Thursday's emergency meeting on the
worsening situation on Kosovo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
